#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.100"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.100:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.100:0.2"
msgid "10. Loṇakapallavagga"
msgstr "10. A Lump of Salt"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.100:0.3"
msgid "100. Loṇakapallasutta"
msgstr "100. A Lump of Salt"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: Yo → yo kho (s1-3, km) | yo ca kho (mr)
msgctxt "an3.100:1.1"
msgid "“Yo, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose you say:"

msgctxt "an3.100:1.2"
msgid ""
"‘yathā yathāyaṃ puriso kammaṃ karoti tathā tathā taṃ paṭisaṃvediyatī’ti, "
"evaṃ santaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyavāso na hoti, okāso na paññāyati sammā "
"dukkhassa antakiriyāya."
msgstr ""
"‘No matter how this person performs a deed, they experience it the same way.’"
" This being so, the spiritual life could not be lived, and there’d be no "
"chance of making a complete end of suffering."

msgctxt "an3.100:1.3"
msgid "Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Suppose you say:"

msgctxt "an3.100:1.4"
msgid ""
"‘yathā yathā vedanīyaṃ ayaṃ puriso kammaṃ karoti tathā tathāssa vipākaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvediyatī’ti, evaṃ santaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyavāso hoti, okāso "
"paññāyati sammā dukkhassa antakiriyāya."
msgstr ""
"‘No matter how this person performs a deed, they experience the result as it "
"should be experienced.’ This being so, the spiritual life can be lived, and "
"there is a chance of making a complete end of suffering."

#. VAR: pāpakammaṃ → pāpaṃ kammaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.100:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ "
"tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti."
msgstr ""
"Take the case of a person who does a trivial bad deed, but it lands them in "
"hell."

msgctxt "an3.100:1.6"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ "
"pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva."
msgstr ""
"While another person does the same trivial bad deed, but experiences it in "
"the present life, without even a bit left over, not to speak of a lot."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.100:2.1"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃrūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upaneti?"
msgstr "What kind of person does a trivial bad deed, but it lands them in hell?"

# Bhavitakaya is explained in MN 36 as ability to endure pain, and also in the same sense at Pe 2. See BB’s note for emendation to dukkhavihari.
msgctxt "an3.100:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo abhāvitakāyo hoti abhāvitasīlo "
"abhāvitacitto abhāvitapañño paritto appātumo appadukkhavihārī."
msgstr ""
"A person who hasn’t developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, or "
"wisdom. They’re small-minded and mean-spirited, living in suffering."

msgctxt "an3.100:2.3"
msgid ""
"Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upaneti."
msgstr "That kind of person does a trivial bad deed, but it lands them in hell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.100:3.1"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃrūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ "
"kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva?"
msgstr ""
"What kind of person does the same trivial bad deed, but experiences it in "
"the present life, without even a bit left over, not to speak of a lot?"

#. VAR: mahatto → mahattā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.100:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo bhāvitakāyo hoti bhāvitasīlo bhāvitacitto "
"bhāvitapañño aparitto mahatto appamāṇavihārī."
msgstr ""
"A person who has developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and "
"wisdom. They’re not small-minded, but are big-hearted, living without limits."

msgctxt "an3.100:3.3"
msgid ""
"Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ "
"diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva."
msgstr ""
"That kind of person does the same trivial bad deed, but experiences it in "
"the present life, without even a bit left over, not to speak of a lot."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.250"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: loṇakapallaṃ → loṇaphalaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: udakamallake → udakakapallake (mr)
msgctxt "an3.100:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso loṇakapallaṃ paritte udakamallake pakkhipeyya."
msgstr "Suppose a person was to drop a lump of salt into a small bowl of water."

msgctxt "an3.100:4.2"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

#. VAR: taṃ parittaṃ udakaṃ → udakamallake udakaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.100:4.3"
msgid "api nu taṃ parittaṃ udakaṃ amunā loṇakapallena loṇaṃ assa apeyyan”ti?"
msgstr "Would that small bowl of water become salty and undrinkable?”"

msgctxt "an3.100:4.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir."

msgctxt "an3.100:4.5"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an3.100:4.6"
msgid ""
"“Aduñhi, bhante, parittaṃ udakakapallake udakaṃ, taṃ amunā loṇakapallena "
"loṇaṃ assa apeyyan”ti."
msgstr "Because there is only a little water in the bowl.”"

msgctxt "an3.100:4.7"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso loṇakapallakaṃ gaṅgāya nadiyā pakkhipeyya."
msgstr "“Suppose a person was to drop a lump of salt into the Ganges river."

msgctxt "an3.100:4.8"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "an3.100:4.9"
msgid "api nu sā gaṅgā nadī amunā loṇakapallena loṇaṃ assa apeyyā”ti?"
msgstr "Would the Ganges river become salty and undrinkable?”"

msgctxt "an3.100:4.10"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir."

msgctxt "an3.100:4.11"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

#. VAR: loṇakapallena loṇo na assa apeyyo”ti → loṇaṃ nevassa appeyyoti (bj) | loṇaphalena loṇo assa apeyyoti (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.100:4.12"
msgid ""
"“Asu hi, bhante, gaṅgāya nadiyā mahā udakakkhandho so amunā loṇakapallena "
"loṇo na assa apeyyo”ti."
msgstr "Because the Ganges river is a vast mass of water.”"

#. </p><p>
