"diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.252"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an3.100:13.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo bhāvitakāyo hoti bhāvitasīlo bhāvitacitto "
"bhāvitapañño aparitto mahatto appamāṇavihārī."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.100:13.2"
msgid ""
"Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ "
"diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.100:13.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, orabbhiko vā urabbhaghātako vā appekaccaṃ urabbhaṃ "
"adinnaṃ ādiyamānaṃ pahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā "
"kātuṃ, appekaccaṃ urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ ādiyamānaṃ nappahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ "
"vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s like a sheep dealer or butcher. They can execute, jail, fine, or "
"otherwise punish one person who steals from them, but not another."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
#. VAR: Kathaṃrūpaṃ → kathaṃrūpo (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "an3.100:14.1"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhikkhave, orabbhiko vā urabbhaghātako vā urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ "
"ādiyamānaṃ pahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kātuṃ?"
msgstr "What kind of person can they punish?"

msgctxt "an3.100:14.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco daliddo hoti appassako appabhogo."
msgstr "A person who is poor, with few possessions and little wealth."

#. VAR: Evarūpaṃ → evarūpo (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "an3.100:14.3"
msgid ""
"Evarūpaṃ, bhikkhave, orabbhiko vā urabbhaghātako vā urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ "
"ādiyamānaṃ pahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kātuṃ."
msgstr "That’s the kind of person they can punish."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
#. VAR: Kathaṃrūpaṃ → kathaṃrūpo (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "an3.100:15.1"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhikkhave, orabbhiko vā urabbhaghātako vā urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ "
"ādiyamānaṃ nappahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā "
"kātuṃ."
msgstr "What kind of person can’t they punish?"

msgctxt "an3.100:15.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco aḍḍho hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo rājā vā "
"rājamahāmatto vā."
msgstr "A person who is rich, affluent, and wealthy."

#. VAR: Evarūpaṃ → evarūpo (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "an3.100:15.3"
msgid ""
"Evarūpaṃ, bhikkhave, orabbhiko vā urabbhaghātako vā urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ "
"ādiyamānaṃ nappahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā "
"kātuṃ."
msgstr "That’s the kind of person they can’t punish."

#. VAR: pañjalikova → pañjaliko (mr)
#. VAR: naṃ → paraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.100:15.4"
msgid "Aññadatthu pañjalikova naṃ yācati:"
msgstr "In fact, all they can do is raise their joined palms and ask:"

msgctxt "an3.100:15.5"
msgid "‘dehi me, mārisa, urabbhaṃ vā urabbhadhanaṃ vā’ti."
msgstr "‘Please, good sir, give me my sheep or pay me for it.’"

msgctxt "an3.100:15.6"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekaccassa puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakampi "
"pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti."
msgstr ""
"This is how it is in the case of a person who does a trivial bad deed, but "
"it lands them in hell."

